There are several other wallet applications/browser extensions that will work with the Bittensor network:

In addition to the Chrome extension https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/bittensor-wallet/bdgmdoedahdcjmpmifafdhnffjinddgc and the iPhone mobile app at  https://apps.apple.com/pl/app/bittensor-wallet/id6476235156 (from the Opentensor team), there are several other options. 

First, there's https://tensorwallet.ca/, by our very own Vune. In addition, most Polkadot ecosystem hot wallets work with TAO, including not just polkadot.js but also Talisman (https://www.talisman.xyz/), SubWallet (https://www.subwallet.app/), and Nova Wallet (https://novawallet.io/). And if you are very security-oriented, there's the air-gapped Polkadot Vault (https://signer.parity.io/#about), which you can run on an old Android phone or iPhone as a cold wallet, as well as Tangem (https://tangem.com/), another cold wallet option. 

Since your tokens exist on-chain and wallets are just interfaces to interact with them (using your seed phrase is allows the wallet interface to generate the public/private keypair that will allow it to authenticate transactions for you on the blockchain), feel free to try a few and see what you like best!

Remember to be very careful with your sensitive account information!  Only people who want to hijack your account will tell you that they need your seed/mnemonic phrase and be especially careful about fake "Bittensor Wallet" websites, which are designed to steal it.

LEDGER DOES NOT CURRENTLY SUPPORT BITTENSOR - this includes using any other wallet software besides Ledger Live (such as Talisman) as an interface to a Ledger device.

Il existe plusieurs autres applications de portefeuille/extensions de navigateur qui fonctionneront avec le réseau Bittensor :

En plus de l'extension Chrome https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/bittensor-wallet/bdgmdoedahdcjmpmifafdhnffjinddgc et de l'application mobile iPhone https://apps.apple.com/pl/app/bittensor-wallet/id6476235156 (de l'équipe Opentensor), il existe plusieurs autres options. 

Tout d'abord, il y a https://tensorwallet.ca/, de notre propre Vune. De plus, la plupart des portefeuilles chauds de l'écosystème Polkadot fonctionnent avec TAO, notamment non seulement polkadot.js , mais aussi Talisman (https://www.talisman.xyz/), SubWallet (https://www.subwallet.app/) et Nova Wallet (https://novawallet.io/). Et si vous êtes très soucieux de la sécurité, il existe le Polkadot Vault (https://signer.parity.io/#about) en mode air-gappé, que vous pouvez exécuter sur un ancien téléphone Android ou un iPhone en tant que portefeuille froid, ainsi que Tangem (https://tangem.com/), une autre option de portefeuille froid. 

Étant donné que vos jetons existent sur la chaîne et que les portefeuilles ne sont que des interfaces pour interagir avec eux (l'utilisation de votre phrase de départ permet à l'interface du portefeuille de générer la paire de clés publique/privée qui lui permettra d'authentifier les transactions pour vous sur la blockchain), n'hésitez pas à en essayer quelques-unes et voyez ce que vous préférez !

The important thing to understand about Bittensor is that it's not like hashrate mining.  Once you have gotten the infrastructure software (Bittensor) installed, the miner or validator codebase is going to be different depending on which subnet(s) you're working in.  There is a very general checklist for preparing to mine or validate here: https://docs.bittensor.com/subnets/checklist-for-validating-mining but it does not contain step-by-step instructions for any particular model or version of node software, which will be subnet-specific.

You can explore the different subnets through the channels in the Subnet and Testnet categories of this Discord. If you have any questions about what equipment/resources/knowledge is required in a particular subnet, check the pinned posts in the subnet's channel.

Note that because the code is different in each subnet, and trying to accomplish something different, it means that there is not really going to be an easy way for us to recommend subnets for newcomers, or for specific computer specifications, etc.  It'll be up to you to figure out which one(s) best match your equipment, resources, and skill level, if you are interested in exploring further. : )

Incentives (rewards for miners) and dividends (rewards for validators and those who delegate stake to validators) automatically compounds and is distributed once per 7200 blocks (about 24 hours); however, the tempo (the actual block number on which this happens) is different for every validator.  If you stake and unstake, it can be up to 48 hours before you'll see dividends, depending on when during the validator's tempo you took the action.  If you are not staking large numbers, it may look as if nothing's happening because most wallet applications round up to two decimal places, which might not be enough to show you that you're actually earning.  That's why I recommend Taostats; the staking information there shows the full 18 decimal places, and also the chart should be showing you a steady upwards trend (as long as you don't do anything to move the stake around, at which point the chart will show some hiccups to reflect that movement).

Les incitations (récompenses pour les mineurs) et les dividendes (récompenses pour les validateurs et ceux qui délèguent la participation aux validateurs) sont automatiquement composés et distribués une fois par 7200 bloc (environ 24 heures) ; cependant, le rythme (le numéro de bloc réel sur lequel cela se produit) est différent pour chaque validateur. Si vous misez et annulez la participation, il peut s'écouler jusqu'à 48 heures avant que vous ne voyiez les dividendes, selon le moment où vous avez effectué l'action pendant le rythme du validateur. Si vous ne misez pas de gros nombres, il peut sembler que rien ne se passe, car la plupart des applications de portefeuille arrondissent à deux décimales, ce qui peut ne pas être suffisant pour vous montrer que vous gagnez réellement.
